==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''genitalia'', substantive use of plural of ''genitalis'' meaning "pertaining to generation or birth", from the Greek ''genete'', (birth).

===Noun===
'''genitalia'''; plural noun

# [[genital]] or sex organs
# a collection of [[gentials]]

====Synonyms====
*[[genitals]] (sense 1)

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[genitaliën]] ''pl'', [[voortplantingsorganen]] ''n, pl''
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Note===
Not used in the singular, which theoretically would be ''genitalium''.

